    <note type="biography">
        <p>American archaeologist and anthropologist. Studied under Louis Agassiz. Curator of several museums in Massachusetts, and superintendent of the Museum of the Essex Institute, Salem, during the 1860s; director, Peabody Academy of Science, Salem, 1869–73, and Peabody Museum of Archaeology and Ethnology, Harvard, from 1874. Permanent secretary, American Association for the Advancement of Science, 1873–98; president from 1898.</p></note>
